{"name": "polars-distance", "metadata": {"name": "polars-distance", "version": "0.5.2", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Programming Language :: Rust"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://ion-elgreco.github.io/polars-distance/", "dependencies": ["polars"], "summary": "Polars plugin for pairwise distance functions", "upload_time": 1734598982}, "documentation": ["Hellooo :)\n\nThis plugin is a work-in progress, main goal is to provide distance metrics on list, arrays and string datatypes.\n\nThe docs can be found here: https://ion-elgreco.github.io/polars-distance/\n\n## Examples\n\n```python\nimport polars\nimport polars_distance as pld\n\ndf = pl.DataFrame({\n    \"foo\":\"hello\",\n    \"bar\":\"hella world\"\n})\n\ndf.select(\n    pld.col(\"foo\").dist_str.hamming('bar').alias('dist')\n)\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502 dist \u2502\n\u2502 ---  \u2502\n\u2502 u32  \u2502\n\u255e\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2561\n\u2502 7    \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n\n\ndf.select(\n    pld.col('foo').dist_str.levenshtein('bar').alias('dist')\n)\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502 dist \u2502\n\u2502 ---  \u2502\n\u2502 u32  \u2502\n\u255e\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2561\n\u2502 6    \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n\n\n\ndf = pl.DataFrame(\n    {\n        \"arr\": [[1, 2, 10]],\n        \"arr2\": [[2, 5, 9]],\n    },\n    schema={\n        \"arr\": pl.Array(inner=pl.Float64, width=3),\n        \"arr2\": pl.Array(inner=pl.Float64, width=3),\n    },\n)\ndf.select(pld.col('arr').dist_arr.euclidean('arr2').alias('dist'))\nshape: (1, 1)\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502 dist     \u2502\n\u2502 ---      \u2502\n\u2502 f64      \u2502\n\u255e\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2561\n\u2502 3.316625 \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_distance_arr", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.data_sets", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_cosine", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_chebyshev", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_canberra", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_bray_curtis", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_manhatten", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_euclidean", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_hamming_str", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_levenshtein", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_distance_arr.test_jaccard_index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data_sets", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns